column5: Hey i was wondering if anyone here knew of any website/service that has updated satellite  images for Northern Ontario? I know that there is google earth and bing maps, but the images from that are from back in 2003-2005. The reason I am asking this is because as most northerners know the logging roads change constantly in the area with some getting blocked off and new ones being built up. It would help me find potential lakes without burning any gas just to find out the roads been dug out.
I don't know if you'll be able to zoom in enough, but here's another site  http://lance-modis.eosdis.nasa.gov/imagery/subsets/?area=na
